div.p:
This review should give attention to, though not be limited by, the
                            following: 

—the prospect for the further spread of radical
                                    government;

—the prospect and likely character of political and economic
                                    cooperation among the North African countries;

—the likely Soviet and radical Arab role in those
                                    countries;

—the role of European countries;

—the relationship of the Arab-Israeli impasse to trends in
                                    North Africa;

—present U.S. programs and policies and resources available
                                    for furtherance of U.S. interests;

—U.S. options in response to trends.
